race.comment: NANTERRE (10) broke the maiden status here last time out and will have taken a bunch of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Maps ideally from gate three and winning rider Mallyon stays on top. Can go right on with the job now. BOLLINGER MISS (6) has been well in the betting at the past few outings and where there's smoke there's fire. Should prove tough to hold out. SANCTUARY STORM (5) resumes here but has won when fresh before and must be respected out of the Archibald camp. Top-three commodity. BROOKLYN DAISY (7) is knocking on the door of another victory hitting the frame in six of her past seven starts. Has to be included in calculations. GAGNANTE ENCHERE (8) goes well for hoop Brooker who has only missed a drum once in five steers and looks one for the multiples.
